# AI Takeoff Lab — frontend environment variables
# Copy to .env.local and fill in values for local development.
# Never commit .env.local or real keys.
#
# Production values (set in Vercel project environment):
#   VITE_SUPABASE_URL      = same Supabase project URL used by all eliteOS heads
#   VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY = same Supabase anon (public) key
#   VITE_BACKEND_URL       = https://backend-core-six.vercel.app
#                            (the canonical eliteOS backend — same URL used by Internal Estimate,
#                             Quote Library, Pricing Admin, etc.)
#
# AI provider keys (OPENAI_API_KEY, GEMINI_API_KEY) are BACKEND-only.
# Do NOT add VITE_OPENAI_API_KEY or VITE_GEMINI_API_KEY here or in any frontend env.
# Do NOT add VITE_SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY — that is backend-only.

VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR_PROJECT.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-supabase-anon-key-here
VITE_BACKEND_URL=http://localhost:3001

# Home Launcher URL — used for brand link and "Open Home" in the user menu.
# Production: https://www.eliteosfab.com
# Leave unset for local dev (defaults to https://www.eliteosfab.com).
# VITE_HEAD_URL_HOME=https://www.eliteosfab.com

# SESSION SHARING NOTE:
# On *.eliteosfab.com, the Supabase session is stored in a .eliteosfab.com-scoped
# cookie (via shared/eliteos-supabase/eliteosSupabaseAuthOptions.ts). This means a
# user signed in at www.eliteosfab.com is automatically recognized at
# takeoff.eliteosfab.com without a separate sign-in — provided VITE_SUPABASE_URL
# and VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY are set to the SAME Supabase project used by Home.
# If these are unset or point to a different project, the session will not be shared.
